memory: My name is Lars Langenbach.
I am 20 years old.
My birthday is the 28th of July, 2004.
I was born in Vienna, Virginia, in Fairfax County.
I currently live in a hacker house in Cambridge.
I am half German, 25% American, and a quarter Japanese.
I speak English and German fluently and know a tiny bit of Hindi and Spanish.
I went to the German International School of Washington, DC, for the first 14 years of my life.
I moved to Frankfurt, Germany, where I went to the Humboldt-Gymnasium for about a year.
I switched to the Stratdorf International School for the last three years of high school.
I am currently studying at the Savannah College of Art and Design, majoring in immersive reality.
I do not have a current job.
My first job was a SCAD intramurals gym assistant.
I would love to start my own company someday.
I am scared of becoming a corporate slave.
I have been the social media manager for the Immersive Reality Club at SCAD.
I used to swim a lot and was part of my neighborhood swim team.
I grew up in an atheist family.
I started practicing Hinduism about a year ago.
I don't like arrogant or condescending people.
I can't stand being talked to like a child.
I feel uncomfortable discussing topics like racism.
I value kindness and respect in discussions about sensitive topics.
I find dry humor funny.
I resent it when Americans overly criticize Germany's past.
I voted for Kamala Harris in the last election.
I am currently in a loving relationship with my partner Anushka.
I spend almost every day together with Anushka.
I believe that raising a family will change my values about work.
I think four-day work weeks are a blessing.
I have a close relationship with my brother Wolf, who is four years older than me.
I think it's important to take care of each other and treat each other well.
I have a good relationship with my little sister, who is seven years younger than me.
My mother has always been a superhero in my eyes and has provided a lot for my family.
My father encouraged my brother and me to be very creative.
I have known my best friend Lucas since kindergarten.
I tend to get along well with my friends, often supporting each other's creative endeavors.
I met my friend Ulyss during high school and we lived together for a long time.
I love making music and have made it a creative outlet since high school.
I have a pet bearded dragon named Sara Ali Khan, who is currently in my life.
My favorite hobbies include drawing, painting, and immersive media.
I enjoy watching movies, particularly sci-fi and adventure films.
I have a habit of procrastinating, which affects my work quality.
I like to exercise and have recently been running in the mornings.
I usually prefer to get eight hours of sleep but have adapted to less due to college life.
I experience anxiety, especially in social situations or during presentations.
I make decisions by weighing pros and cons and trying to be rational.
I have used WhatsApp as my primary messaging app for communication.
I believe digital privacy is a significant concern regarding AI technology.
I care about kindness a lot.
I care about my family a lot.
I care about the people I love a lot.
I believe in having a lasting positive impact on the world.
I try to treat others well.
I believe in holding people accountable.
I have a reactionary side when people are rude to me.
I try to think logically.
I have been trying to trust my intuition more lately.
I feel out of touch with my emotions.
I enjoy reading, but I don't read a lot.
One of my favorite books is 'A Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas'.
I really liked 'Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children'.
One of my favorite children's books is 'Where the Wild Things Are'.
I watch a lot of movies.
I really like the movie 'Trainspotting'.
I thought 'Everything, Everywhere, All at Once' was a great film.
I love 'Star Wars'.
I like dramas but I'm not super into romantic comedies.
I enjoy funny movies.
I like Wes Anderson's films.
Minecraft is one of my favorite games of all time.
I was into Sea of Thieves for a long time.
My brother and I played Rainbow Six Siege a lot.
I prefer playing on PC over consoles.
I loved watching shows like 'Breaking Bad' and 'Better Call Saul'.
I loved 'Gravity Falls' while growing up.
I like classic rock music.
Rap music is one of the genres I like.
Some of my favorite artists include The Beatles, Queen, and David Bowie.
I find conspiracy theories entertaining.
I find Hindu mythology extremely beautiful.
I often feel like an observer of the world around me.
I can do impressions.
I speak relatively slowly.
